But I will say, from an
astrobiology perspective, one

00:35:15.300 --> 00:35:17.250
of the amazing things
about New Horizons

00:35:17.250 --> 00:35:20.910
and Pluto is the
evidence that there

00:35:20.910 --> 00:35:27.060
is an ocean of liquid water
beneath the icy crust of Pluto.

00:35:27.060 --> 00:35:30.180
It seems like there's
circumstantial evidence

00:35:30.180 --> 00:35:32.520
that there are features
of the planet that

00:35:32.520 --> 00:35:35.312
are easiest to explain if
there is a liquid water ocean.

00:35:35.312 --> 00:35:37.020
And one of the things
we would definitely

00:35:37.020 --> 00:35:39.390
want to do with this orbiter
Alan is talking about

00:35:39.390 --> 00:35:43.980
if we go back is map
the gravity field

00:35:43.980 --> 00:35:45.934
and do other things
to really make sure we

00:35:45.934 --> 00:35:47.100
understand that that's true.

00:35:47.100 --> 00:35:50.070
But it's seeming like there is
an ocean of liquid water, which

00:35:50.070 --> 00:35:52.200
is amazing from an
astrobiology perspective

00:35:52.200 --> 00:35:55.470
because any place where
